ts hands resembles the colorful faces of the invaders in the {{wp|The War of the Worlds (1953 film)|1953 \'\'War of the Worlds\'\' film}}; however, the aliens in the film had green, blue, and red dots while Elgyem has red, green, and yellow. Judging from its Pokédex entry, Elgyem and its {{p|Beheeyem|evolution}} may also be based on the {{wp|Area 51}} {{wp|Area 51#UFO and other conspiracy theories|alien conspiracy theories}} or the {{wp|Roswell UFO incident|Roswell incident}}. Considering its species names, physical appearance, and powers, it may also be based on a {{wp|brain}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nElgyem is a corruption of the abbreviation \'\'{{wp|Little green men|LGM}}\'\', a common term used to refer to extraterrestrials.\n\nLigray may be derived from \'\'{{wp|Grey alien|greys}}\'\' (a commonly speculated type of extraterrestrial) and may also be a combination of \'\'light\'\' (as in light-grey) or \'\'little\'\' and \'\'grey\'\' (alternative spelling of \'\'gray\'\'). Alternatively, it may be a combination of \'\'little\'\' and a corruption of \'\'green\'\', referring to the slang for aliens: "little green men."\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Psychic|type2=Psychic\n|ja=リグレー \'\'Ligray\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'{{wp|Grey alien|greys}}\'\'; possibly also a contraction of {{tt|リットルグリーンマン|Little Green Man}}\n|fr=Lewsor|frmeaning=A reversed corruption of \'\'{{wp|Roswell UFO incident|Roswell}}\'\'\n|es=Elgyem|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Pygraulon|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Pygmäe|pygmy}}\'\', \'\'{{tt|grau|gray}}\'\', and \'\'encephalon\'\'\n|it=Elgyem|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=리그레 \'\'Ligray\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=小灰怪 \'\'Xiǎo\u200bhuī\u200bguài\u200b\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Little grey freak". Possibly a reference to {{wp|Greys|{{tt|小灰人 \'\'xiǎohuīrén\'\'|Greys}}}}\n|ru=Элгием \'\'Elgiem\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n|sr=Eldžijem|srmeaning=From English name\n}}\n<br clear="left